article.headline: TCU 71, Houston 65
article.story: FORT WORTH, Texas (AP) -- Marcus Shropshire scored 27 points and Corey Santee added 12 points and seven assists as TCU came back to beat Houston 71-65 Saturday night. TCU (11-14, 7-7 Conference USA) trailed for most of the game until Femi Ibukunle's free throw with 4:03 left to put the Horned Frogs up 61-60 and give them the lead for good. Andre Owens led Houston (9-16, 3-11) with 22 points, and Marcus Oliver added 15. Lanny Smith scored 11 points. TCU struggled in the first half, hitting just 31 percent of its shots and trailing 34-26 at halftime. But then the Horned Frogs hit 65 percent (13-of-20) in the second half. Shropshire finished 8-of-15 from the field, including 7-of-13 on 3-pointers. The Horned Frogs clinched a spot in the Conference USA tournament.
